Wrapper for Yield Math Smart Contract Library.

params.k: time till maturity coefficient, multiplied by 2^64

returns._0: the amount of DAI a user would have to pay for given amount of         yDAI

params.k: time till maturity coefficient, multiplied by 2^64

params.x: number to raise into given power y/z
params.y: numerator of the power to raise x into
params.z: denominator of the power to raise x into

returns._0: x raised into power y/z and then multiplied by 2^(128 * (1 - y/z))

params.x: power to raise 2 into, multiplied by 2^121

log_2(uint128).notice: Calculate base 2 logarithm of an unsigned 128-bit integer number.  Revert in case x is zero.

pow(uint128,uint128,uint128).notice: Raise given number x into power specified as a simple fraction y/z and then multiply the result by the normalization factor 2^(128 * (1 - y/z)). Revert if z is zero, or if both x and y are zeros.
